-- Clinton says agreement "in principle" with UBS
-- 
-- Fri Jul 31, 2009 9:49am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/07/31/us-ubs-tax-clinton-sb-idUSTRE56U3D920090731

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - U.S. Secretary of State Hillary Clinton said on Friday there had been an agreement "in principle" with Switzerland over a tax case involving Swiss bank UBS. 

 "There has been agreement reached in the litigation," Clinton said before a meeting with Switzerland's foreign minister. Asked if there were any outstanding issues in the case, Clinton said the agreement had been reached "in principle." (Reporting by  Sue Pleming ; Editing by  Bill Trott )